Code Tenderloin

Code Tenderloin is a non-profit organization that teaches programming and economic empowerment to students with unfavorable backgrounds, in order to provide them with more opportunities and reduce the inequality of work that exists in the field of technology in San Francisco and the bay area. I am currently a TA in Code Tenderloin, in the Code Ramp ++ program, where JavaScript is taught. I give programming classes, mock interviews and extra class consultations.
